1554
02:10:04,984 --> 02:10:07,407
I'll tell you firsthand, it's happening in this community.

1555
02:10:07,948 --> 02:10:10,872
And we're asking residents to make that decision.

1556
02:10:11,809 --> 02:10:14,311
So I just want people to be aware of that.

1557
02:10:15,092 --> 02:10:29,463
What about the young families that paid top dollar for their home and brought in this community recently and have to decide whether their child will play sports, whether they'll go on vacation, whether they'll save for their college tuition.

1558
02:10:30,805 --> 02:10:33,547
These are the decisions that have to be made.

1559
02:10:34,488 --> 02:10:38,271
So it's easy to say, hey, look what 12 million will do for us.

1560
02:10:39,703 --> 02:10:42,746
But what's the collateral damage to that 12 million?

1561
02:10:43,888 --> 02:10:45,549
It's the seniors on fixed income.

1562
02:10:46,010 --> 02:10:47,031
It's the families.

1563
02:10:47,391 --> 02:10:50,915
It's the renters that Councilor Caviello has mentioned in the past.

1564
02:10:52,136 --> 02:10:55,520
Many people, many landlords are going to pass this on to the renters.

1565
02:10:56,501 --> 02:10:57,562
And that's what's going to happen.

1566
02:10:58,512 --> 02:11:12,258
And as Councilor Caviello mentioned, what about the seniors in this community that brought their home 25, 30, 40 years ago in a property rich, like Councilor Caviello says, and income poor?

1567
02:11:12,278 --> 02:11:17,341
$500, I would submit to you, is a lot of money.

1568
02:11:17,981 --> 02:11:22,003
It's a lot of money for people on fixed incomes.

1569
02:11:23,396 --> 02:11:30,081
So I think, you know, when you talk about a cavalier, cavalier saying that, well, it's only 500, it's only 550.

1570
02:11:31,121 --> 02:11:36,145
And, you know, I think you gotta be mindful of who is living in this community.

1571
02:11:36,465 --> 02:11:41,208
And my last point, and I appreciate the time, believe me, and I don't wanna take up any more time.

1572
02:11:41,729 --> 02:11:43,370
We're in a time of uncertainty.

1573
02:11:43,790 --> 02:11:45,171
We're talking about inflation.

1574
02:11:45,431 --> 02:11:46,973
We're talking about recession.

1575
02:11:47,813 --> 02:11:53,298
